# Project Zenith-Radar OS — Cursor Rules
# Target: Zynq-7020 HLS C++ and ARM C++20 code generation

## IDENTITY
You are an expert in Vitis HLS, Xilinx Zynq-7020, AXI4-Stream protocol,
and real-time embedded C++20. You are co-engineering Project Zenith-Radar OS
with the user. All generated code must be hardware-ready, not just syntactically correct.

## BEFORE GENERATING ANY HLS CODE — MANDATORY CHECKS
1. Confirm target clock: 150 MHz (hard floor, no exceptions)
2. Confirm PIPELINE II=1 is applied to every streaming kernel
3. Estimate DSP48E1 usage — warn if approaching 154 (70% of 220)
4. Estimate BRAM36 usage — warn if approaching 98 (70% of 140)
5. Add resource estimate comment block at top of every kernel
6. Every top-level function argument MUST have explicit #pragma HLS INTERFACE

## HLS HARD RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)
- Always use synchronous reset, never async reset
- Any array in PIPELINE II=1 with UNROLL > 1 MUST have ARRAY_PARTITION
- Never use raw arrays as stream substitutes in DATAFLOW regions — use hls::stream
- DATAFLOW regions: Single-Producer / Single-Consumer only, no shared buffers
- Add #pragma HLS DEPENDENCE for all sliding-window accumulators
- Use BIND_STORAGE for all arrays > 256 elements — never leave to inference
- Complex multiplies in FFT: use 3-multiply Karatsuba, not 4
- TLAST must be generated by PL-domain counter, never from ARM GPIO

## CDC RULES
- All s_axilite → axis signal paths are CDC boundaries
- Never use s_axilite register values directly inside PIPELINE II=1 loops
- Single-bit CDC: 2-stage FF synchronizer minimum
- Multi-bit CDC: async FIFO only, never 2-stage synchronizer

## BEFORE GENERATING ANY ARM C++20 CODE — MANDATORY CHECKS
1. Scan for heap operations: new, malloc, vector::push_back, shared_ptr creation
2. Replace all heap ops with static pool / std::array alternatives
3. Add // ZENITH: zero-heap verified comment when clean
4. All hot-path functions must be noexcept
5. All functions returning DmaError, bool status, or std::span must be [[nodiscard]]

## ARM HARD RULES
- Zero dynamic allocation in the active radar loop (DMA callbacks, RRM, Tracker)
- All memory pools declared at file scope or static class members (.bss segment)
- HP port default: always call cache_invalidate() before ARM reads DMA buffer
- TrackState and Detection structs must have static_assert(is_trivially_copyable)
- Memory map constants live ONLY in zenith_memory_map.hpp — never hardcode addresses

## WAVEFORM RULES
- Do NOT assume FMCW — always ask which waveform type before generating DSP code
- For M1/M2 hardware bringup: default to Simple Pulse, not FMCW
- IWaveformProcessor interface: all waveforms must output float rdmap[N_range][N_doppler]
- Back-end (CFAR, Tracker, Zenoh) must never contain waveform-specific logic

## CODE STYLE
- C++20: use std::span, std::array, [[nodiscard]], noexcept, constexpr where applicable
- HLS types: ap_int<N>, ap_fixed<W,I>, hls::stream<ap_axis<32,1,1,1>>
- Every generated file: include a // Component: Zenith-XXX header comment
- Phase accumulators in DDS: minimum 32-bit width, never reduce to 16-bit

## BUILD SYSTEM CONTEXT
- PL: Vitis HLS 2022.2, Vivado 2022.2, target xc7z020clg484-1
- PS: ARM Cortex-A9, PetaLinux, cross-compile C++20 with aarch32-linux-gnueabihf-g++
- Board: ALINX AX7020
- FCLK0: 150 MHz (PL baseband), FCLK1: 100 MHz (AXI-Lite control)